text: @misscalcul8 So 4x gets to 2pi 4 times as fast as just an x does. We go through the whole cycle by the time we get to pi/2. If we draw that, it's gonna look horizontally compressed, but it corresponding to running through cycles faster.
bbox_coords: NA NA NA NA NA NA NA NA
name: Suzanne von Oy
description: Graph Specialist and Interaction Developer at Desmos. Former HS math teacher in Connecticut.

text: @misscalcul8 One way I've thought of this is to say that the argument (I'll call it the angle) is now 4x instead of just x. So I ask myself when does the angle equal zero, and when does it equal 2pi? 4x=0 at 0, so a period starts at 0, & gets to the full 2pi at 4x=2pi so when x = 2pi/4.
